<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="1064" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1064">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/3745.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consular Agent <persName type="from">Ulmer</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Ciudad, Juarez</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-23">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 23, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>I beg that you advise me immediately what I shall do in behalf of
                            Americans at Torreon, Velardena, and Durango, eighty-five in number.
                            These citizens depend on me solely and entirely for instructions as to
                            their safety. My telegrams to them on the situation are either refused
                            or delayed. Must I send special messenger? Wire me immediately, care
                            Hotel Sheldon.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">I. M. Ulmer</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>